==English==

===Etymology===
Origin of the word is subject to much debate but most pundits credit it to ex-player and now manager of [[Crystal Palace F.C.]] [[Iain Dowie]] in reference to his team's unexpected return to winning form.

===Adjective===
'''bouncebackability'''

#The ability of a person or team to [[bounce back]], that is, to return to good form after a period of not performing well.
#: ''By passing the test, after last years abysmal failure, he exhibited great bouncebackability.''

